text: Peter Moore (1940–2010) was an Irish sportsperson. He played Gaelic football for his local club Ballinabrackey and was a senior member of the Meath county team from 1959 until 1970. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:2010 deaths Category:Gaelic football managers Category:Meath inter-county Gaelic footballers
title: Peter Moore (Gaelic footballer)
